{
  "texts": [
    "These models suggest specific opinion-formation dynamics based on what other humans, texts, images, etc.",
    "an individual interacts with.",
    "By extension, we could consider the generalization of these networks to the case where LLMs play a key role as (possibly influential) nodes, or as determining how an individual navigates a knowledge graph.",
    "One of the key ideas of Web 2.0 was that users, not just authors or programmers, structure the knowledge (O'Reilly 2005).",
    "By extension, in the AI era, LLMs interact with users, authors, programmers and technology to structure that knowledge, and understanding the flow of information requires understanding the emergent behavior of these elements."
  ]
}